-- Dubai Government Has No Current Plans to Implement Income, Corporate Taxes
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-09-27T11:36:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/dubai-government-has-no-current-plans-to-implement-income-corporate-taxes.html
Dubai has no current plans to
implement income or corporate taxes, the government said in an
updated bond prospectus published on the London Stock Exchange.  “The Dubai government has no plans currently to implement
income or corporation taxes, although there has been speculation
in relation to a federal government imposed value added tax
regime for some time,” according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  